## Additional Considerations for 2026

### Battery Health and Longevity

When purchasing a refurbished or older iPhone, always check the battery health. Apple’s Battery Health feature provides insights into the device’s maximum capacity and performance. A battery with at least 80% capacity is generally considered good for daily use.

### Warranty and Return Policies

Opt for sellers offering warranties or return policies. This adds an extra layer of security in case the device doesn’t meet expectations. Apple’s Certified Refurbished program is a trusted option, providing a one-year warranty.

### The Role of 5G in 2026

With 5G networks becoming the norm in 2026, choosing a device with 5G capabilities ensures faster internet speeds and smoother connectivity. Models like the **iPhone SE (3rd Gen)** and **iPhone 12** are excellent choices for future-proofing your purchase.

